{"questionId":"9074227","questionHtml":"<p>In a photoelectric experiment a stopping voltage <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi></math></em> required to prevent photoelectrons from flowing across the photoelectric cell is measured for light of two frequencies <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>. The results obtained are shown.<img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/446da27d8077d91559521870cad3a9788b45a8b7.png\"></p>\n<p>The ratio <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;is an estimate of</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>e</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>e</mi><mi>h</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>e</mi></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074227","referenceCode":"21N.1.HL.TZ0.37","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"In a photoelectric experiment a stopping voltage V required to prevent photoelectrons from flowing across the photoelectric cell is measured for light of two frequencies f1 and f2.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"37","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 12: Quantum and nuclear physics","12.1 – The interaction of matter with radiation","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 12: Quantum and nu